from pyspark.sql import SparkSession

# Azure storage access info
blob_account_name = 'videogamedevdls' # replace with your blob name
blob_container_name = 'videogamedevfs' # replace with your container name
linked_service_name = 'videogamedevsyn-WorkspaceDefaultStorage' # replace with your linked service name

blob_sas_token = mssparkutils.credentials.getConnectionStringOrCreds(linked_service_name)

# Allow SPARK to access from Blob remotely

spark.conf.set('fs.azure.sas.%s.%s.dfs.core.windows.net' % (blob_container_name, blob_account_name), blob_sas_token)

blob_relative_path = f'silver/{table}/{table}.parquet' # replace with your relative folder path
wasb_path = 'abfss://%s@%s.dfs.core.windows.net/%s' % (blob_container_name, blob_account_name, blob_relative_path)
print('Remote blob path: ' + wasb_path)
df = spark.read.parquet(wasb_path)
